dct_title_s: Sketch map of north eastern India, with portions of Burmah & China to accompany the paper by Genl. Sir Arthur Cotton, R.E.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Sir A. Cotton's proposed line [canal] shown in red. Includes inset: The frontiers of Assam, Burmah & China on an enlarged scale [ ca. 1:2,168,000]. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 37, (1867), p. 231-39; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.37 1867
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1867.
